cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design and optimization of a virtual FD-enabled small cell network with cache and MEC for heterogeneous services. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the allocation of resources for user association, power control, caching, and computing offloading policies. This requires the use of information theory concepts and techniques. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes an ADMM algorithm for obtaining the optimal solution to the formulated resource allocation problem. This involves distributed computing and parallel processing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the optimization of a complex system involving multiple components such as caching, computing offloading, and FD communication. This requires the use of systems and control theory. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers two heterogeneous services, high-data-rate service and computation-sensitive service. This involves the transmission and processing of multimedia data, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
